&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GREATER MANCHESTER MENTAL HEALTH NHS FOUNDATION TRUST (GMMH)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;0.2 WTE/7.5hrs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 8A Specialist Psychosexual Therapist &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;(Applications from less experienced candidates may be considered for appointment at Band 7 and be supported to achieve competencies required for 8A through a preceptorship arrangement)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;____________________________________________________________&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rawnsley Building, Manchester Royal Infirmary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible working, to include remote working some/all of the time may be supported based on service needs/service developments/service user requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent opportunity to join our established Psychosexual Service. You will be based at our Central Manchester site but may be able to perform some or all of your role remotely (we welcome expressions of interest in remote working from experienced therapists).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced and enthusiastic psychosexual therapist with an appreciation of the challenges and rewards of working within a culturally diverse city.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service sits within the Central Manchester and Citywide operational division of GMMH, a large mental health trust (created in 2017). You would be joining a small but highly experienced team of established psychosexual therapists, and you would be supported/line managed by the clinical lead for the service. A high standard of supervision and potential opportunities for career development exist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameEmma MathewsJob titlePsychosexual TherapistEmail addressemma.mathews@gmmh.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gill Brisk (Psychosexual Therapist)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;gillian.brisk@gmmh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
